net.kemuri9.type

Class TypeVariableImpl<D extends GenericDeclaration>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.kemuri9.type.AnnotatedElementImpl
      • net.kemuri9.type.TypeVariableImpl<D>
  • Type Parameters:
    D - the type of generic declaration that declared the underlying type variable.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    AnnotatedElement, Type, TypeVariable<D>

    public class TypeVariableImpl<D extends GenericDeclaration>
extends AnnotatedElementImpl
implements TypeVariable<D>
    An implementation of TypeVariable for use when necessary. It is unwise to actually use this in wide practice. This is due to a restriction in the core TypeVariable implementation to where it is only equivalent to its own type; it is not equivalent to other TypeVariable implementations that have the same attributes. see JDK-8031984 and JDK-8039163 which state that this is an intended behavior of the core implementation.
